# Small Business Security

> Practical cybersecurity resources and guidance for small businesses

[![Website](https://img.shields.io/website?url=https%3A%2F%2Fsmallbizsecurity.org)](https://smallbizsecurity.org)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Contributions Welcome](https://img.shields.io/badge/contributions-welcome-brightgreen.svg)](CONTRIBUTING.md)

## About

Small Business Security (smallbizsecurity.org) is a comprehensive resource platform designed to help small and medium-sized businesses implement effective cybersecurity measures without breaking the bank. We provide actionable guidance, tools, and best practices tailored specifically for businesses with limited IT resources and budgets.

## Mission

To democratize cybersecurity by making enterprise-level security practices accessible and affordable for small businesses, helping them protect their data, customers, and reputation from cyber threats.

## Features

- **Security Assessments** - Self-guided security audits and checklists
- **Implementation Guides** - Step-by-step tutorials for security tools and practices
- **Resource Library** - Curated collection of free and affordable security tools
- **Incident Response Planning** - Templates and guidance for breach preparedness
- **Compliance Assistance** - Help navigating regulatory requirements
- **Threat Intelligence** - Current threat landscape updates relevant to small businesses

## Target Audience

- Small business owners (1-50 employees)
- Entrepreneurs and startups
- Small business IT administrators
- Business consultants and advisors
- Anyone seeking practical cybersecurity guidance

## Key Topics Covered

### Essential Security Practices
- Password management and multi-factor authentication
- Email security and phishing prevention
- Secure remote work policies
- Data backup and recovery strategies
- Network security fundamentals

### Compliance & Legal
- GDPR, CCPA, and privacy law guidance
- Industry-specific compliance (HIPAA, PCI-DSS)
- Cyber insurance considerations
- Legal incident response requirements

### Tools & Technologies
- Antivirus and endpoint protection
- VPN setup and management
- Cloud security best practices
- Mobile device management
- Security awareness training platforms

## Getting Started

### For Website Users
1. Visit [smallbizsecurity.org](https://smallbizsecurity.org)
2. Take our free security assessment
3. Browse resources relevant to your industry
4. Download our starter security checklist
5. Join our community newsletter

### For Contributors
1. Fork this repository
2. Read our [Contributing Guidelines](CONTRIBUTING.md)
3. Check the [Issues](https://github.com/smallbizsecurity/smallbizsecurity.org/issues) for areas needing help
4. Submit pull requests with improvements

## Repository Structure

```
smallbizsecurity.org/
├── content/                 # Website content and articles
│   ├── guides/             # Security implementation guides
│   ├── tools/              # Tool reviews and comparisons
│   ├── resources/          # Downloadable resources
│   └── blog/               # News and updates
├── assets/                 # Images, documents, and media
├── templates/              # Document and policy templates
├── scripts/                # Automation and utility scripts
├── docs/                   # Technical documentation
└── community/              # Community guidelines and resources
```

## Contributing

We welcome contributions from cybersecurity professionals, small business owners, and anyone passionate about improving small business security. Ways to contribute:

- **Content Creation** - Write guides, reviews, or blog posts
- **Technical Review** - Help verify accuracy of security advice
- **Translation** - Make content accessible in multiple languages
- **User Testing** - Provide feedback on usability and effectiveness
- **Bug Reports** - Report website issues or outdated information

Please read our [Contributing Guidelines](CONTRIBUTING.md) and [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) before getting started.

